{"questionId":"14078","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The following diagram shows a right triangle ABC. Point D lies on AB such that CD&nbsp;bisects AĈB.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/9458b833ab138b0d6ccd877fdee6a3dbab62da86.png\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">AĈD = <em>θ</em> and AC = 14 cm</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the value of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{cos}}\\,2\\theta \"> <mrow> <mtext>cos</mtext> </mrow> <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace> <mn>2</mn> <mi>θ</mi> </math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>correct substitution into&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{cos}}\\,2\\theta \"> <mrow> <mtext>cos</mtext> </mrow> <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace> <mn>2</mn> <mi>θ</mi> </math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>eg&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</em> <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"2\\left( {\\frac{{16}}{{25}}} \\right) - 1\"> <mn>2</mn> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <mfrac> <mrow> <mn>16</mn> </mrow> <mrow> <mn>25</mn> </mrow> </mfrac> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> <mo>−</mo> <mn>1</mn> </math></span>,&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"1 - 2{\\left( {\\frac{3}{5}} \\right)^2}\"> <mn>1</mn> <mo>−</mo> <mn>2</mn> <mrow> <msup> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <mfrac> <mn>3</mn> <mn>5</mn> </mfrac> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> </math></span>,&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{16}}{{25}} - \\frac{9}{{25}}\"> <mfrac> <mrow> <mn>16</mn> </mrow> <mrow> <mn>25</mn> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>−</mo> <mfrac> <mn>9</mn> <mrow> <mn>25</mn> </mrow> </mfrac> </math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{cos}}\\,2\\theta&nbsp; = \\frac{7}{{25}}\"> <mrow> <mtext>cos</mtext> </mrow> <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace> <mn>2</mn> <mi>θ</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mfrac> <mn>7</mn> <mrow> <mn>25</mn> </mrow> </mfrac> </math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1&nbsp; &nbsp;N2</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"14078","referenceCode":"19M.1.SL.TZ1.S_3b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the value of cos 2 θ .","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.2—2d and 3d trig, sine rule, cosine rule, area"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}